<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-130-256 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 844 232</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 13 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MS-DOS 5.0 discounts for large sites. (Microsoft Corp. marketingstrategy)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Marketing).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   MS-DOS 5.0 (Operating system) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Operating systemsMarketing StrategyPromotion of ProductDiscount.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MS-DOS 5.0 DISCOUNTS FOR LARGE SITES 06/13/91 REDMOND, WASHINGTON, U.S.A.,andO;1991 JUN 13 (NB) -- Microsoft has announced that it will offer significantdiscounts for large sites that want to upgrade all of their DOS based PCs toVersion 5.andM;Titled the MS-DOS 5 upgrade 100% Program, companies will be able to upgradeto Version 5 for as low as $37 per PC.andP;  The suggested list price for singleuser upgrades is $99.95, or $79.95 for the Microsoft License Pak.andM;An additional benefit of the new program is that the customer will not haveto have multiple licenses on hand, or multiple copies the documentation whichwould come with single copy upgrade packages.andM;To qualify for the program, user companies must have at least 100 DOS basedPCs at one or more locations, and must upgrade all of their DOS-based PCs.andO;Once the company signs the 100% Program agreement, they receive a singlelicense to install the upgrades on any number of machines.andM;The per-machine price for the 100% program is determined by the number ofDOS-based machines in the company.andP;  For less than 1000 PCs, the cost is $59per machine.andP;  Users with 100 but less than 5000 machines can upgrade for $44each, while companies with 5000 or more PCs will pay the $37 fee.andM;For smaller companies which can't meet the 100 minimum, or who for somereason don't want to upgrade all of their machines, an optional discount planis available.andP;  Microsoft offers the License Pak, which provides an upgradepackage for $79.95 per machine.andP;  Additional copies of documentation areavailable for $20 each if the customer upgrades via the 100% program or theLicense Pak.andM;DOS users can obtain the name of the nearest 100% program reseller by calling800-992-3675(DOS5).andM;(Jim Mallory/19910612/Press Contact: Microsoft, Liz Sidnam, 206-882-8080)</TEXT></DOC>